description:
Have you enlisted in the army of the Lord? An unseen war is being waged that is as real as any earthly war, but the stakes are far higher. It is a privilege to be called into the army of the Lord at the eleventh hour and receive the same wages, eternal life. But the conflict is nonetheless intense. The army of the Lord is so unlike any earthly army that it takes a total transformation of mind and character to even survive in it because the greatest battle in this unseen war is not with an enemy on the field. It’s the battle against self.

In 1 Chronicles 11, God gave David’s mighty men great victory over their enemies. Who were these warriors of God that made up the army of the Lord? What lessons can we glean for the battles we face in our own lives? In this sermon, Walter Veith analyzes 1 Chronicles 11, plumbing the depths of the typology in these verses. He reminds us that Christ will conquer the opposition—including the sin that lives in each of us.

Learn the importance and joy of joining the Lord’s army. Our General has never lost a battle and has promised victory in the end. What part will you play in the closing conflict?
